@page "/about-us"

<div class="space-y-8 md:space-y-10">
    <section class="surface-panel rope-border rounded-[2rem] p-6 md:p-8">
        <SectionHeader Eyebrow="About The Voyage" Title="An artist site rebuilt like a sea-worn listening room" Description="This redesign reframes Collin's catalog as an immersive story space: part festival archive, part warm analog control booth, part fan-facing home base." />
        <div class="mt-8 grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-3">
            <div class="rounded-[1.5rem] border border-theme bg-accent-soft p-5">
                <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.35em] text-muted">Vision</div>
                <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-7 text-[var(--fg)]">Put the music first, then wrap it in a memorable atmosphere that feels focused, tactile, and unmistakably handcrafted.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-[1.5rem] border border-theme bg-accent-soft p-5">
                <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.35em] text-muted">Aesthetic</div>
                <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-7 text-[var(--fg)]">A single scarlet accent, restrained neutrals, metallic controls, and layered surfaces instead of a scattered multi-color palette.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-[1.5rem] border border-theme bg-black/5 p-5 dark:bg-white/5">
                <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.35em] text-muted">Experience</div>
                <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-7 text-[var(--fg)]">A routed Blazor app with a persistent top player, reusable card primitives, and theme state that survives refreshes across the whole site.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-[1.05fr_0.95fr]">
        <div class="surface-panel rope-border rounded-[2rem] p-6 md:p-8">
            <div class="section-label">Story</div>
            <div class="mt-6 space-y-5 text-sm leading-8 text-muted md:text-base">
                <p>Collin's catalog lives in the overlap between festival energy and melodic sentimentality. That balance is what shaped the new information architecture: fast access to tracks, a player that feels tactile, and supporting pages that give the artist narrative room to breathe.</p>
                <p>The site now behaves like a proper artist hub instead of a transplanted template. Routing is conventional, the design system is shared across pages, and the player state belongs to the app instead of a one-off layout switch statement.</p>
                <p>Light and dark mode are both first-class. The bright theme keeps surfaces clean and bright while the dark theme shifts the same system into a late-night booth, both anchored by the same #AC0808 accent.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="surface-panel rope-border rounded-[2rem] p-6 md:p-8">
            <div class="section-label">What Changed</div>
            <div class="mt-6 space-y-4">
                <div class="rounded-[1.5rem] border border-theme px-4 py-4">
                    <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.35em] text-accent">Tailwind Foundation</div>
                    <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-7 text-muted">The app now has a real Tailwind build path and a single compiled stylesheet instead of a stack of legacy vendor CSS files.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="rounded-[1.5rem] border border-theme px-4 py-4">
                    <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.35em] text-accent">Shared Mixer State</div>
                    <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-7 text-muted">The top player and DJ room share one playback state, so queue, track metadata, timeline, and volume stay in sync across routes.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="rounded-[1.5rem] border border-theme px-4 py-4">
                    <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.35em] text-accent">Content-Led Pages</div>
                    <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-7 text-muted">Home, releases, profile, and about now each have distinct jobs instead of all inheriting the same template furniture.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</div>



